Package com.sicomsa.dmt.util

Class SOAPUtils

java.lang.Object
com.sicomsa.dmt.util.SOAPUtils
public final class SOAPUtils extends Object
Helper class that provides simple methods for parsing SOAPMessages; converting messages to String or from String; and saving or reading them from file.

1.0

    • parseGrandchild

      public static jakarta.xml.soap.SOAPElement parseGrandchild(jakarta.xml.soap.SOAPElement parent, QName son, QName grandchild)
      Gets the immediate child Node of perent element with the name son and from that found element, gets the immediate child Node with the name grandchild and returns de Node as a SOAPElement. Or it will throw SvcParceException if son or granchild were not found.

      It is important to consider that this method is mostly used when a parent Node should only have one child Node with a particular name and that that child element will only have a child Node with an also particular name. Since this method only seeks the immediate child Node at each search.

      Parameters:
      parent - the element to seek for the son element
      son - the name of the element to find in parent
      grandchild - the name of the element to find from the son found element
      Returns:
      the immediate child Node of the element with the name specified in thegranchild parameter, from the immediate child Node of the element whit the name specified in the son parameter, from the element parent.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - y element or qname are null
      SvcParseException - if the son element could not be found or if the granchild element could not be found.

    • parseChild

      public static jakarta.xml.soap.SOAPElement parseChild(jakarta.xml.soap.SOAPElement element, QName qname)
      Returns the immediate child Node of the given element with the specified name, as a SOAPElement. This method will throw a SvcParseException if the Node was not found.
      Parameters:
      element - the element to parse
      qname - the name of the element to find
      Returns:
      the immediate child Node of the given element with the specified name, as a SOAPElement. This method will throw a SvcParseException if the Node was not found.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - y element or qname are null
      SvcParseException - if the element did not have a child with the given qname.

    • parseChild

      public static jakarta.xml.soap.SOAPElement parseChild(jakarta.xml.soap.SOAPElement element, QName qname, boolean required)
      Returns the immediate child Node of the given element with the specified name, as a SOAPElement. Or null if child is not found and not required. If required and not found then it will throw and exception.
      Parameters:
      element - the element to parse
      qname - the name of the element to find
      required - if true child must be found or throw exception
      Returns:
      the immediate child Node of the given element with the specified name, as a SOAPElement. Or null if child is not found and not required. If required and not found then it will throw and exception.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - y element or qname are null
      SvcParseException - if it was required to find the element and the element did not have a child with the given qname.
